<1ST_LINE>r i PM-Obit-Vu     09-01 0120</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-Obit-Vu,0123</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Noted Vietnamese Writer Dies in Traffic Accident</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BANGKOK, Thailand (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Luu Quang Vu, a noted Vietnamese
playwright, was killed in a traffic accident near Hanoi earlier
this week, the official Vietnam News Agency said today. He was 40.
   The agency, monitored in Bangkok, said Vu's wife, poet Xuan
Quynh, and their 13-year-old son also died in the accident Monday
near the Vietnamese capital.
   ``Luu Quang Vu is author of many well-known plays which put him
at the fore of present-day Vietnamese dramatists,'' the agency said.
   Many of his works have been televised and his last play, a
comedy entitled ``Keeping Up Appearances,'' was being staged in
Hanoi, it said.
   No details were given on funeral arrangements.
</TEXT>
