<1ST_LINE>r a PM-OfficerShot     09-01 0218</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-Officer Shot,230</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Police Officer Shot to Death in Drug Raid</HEAD>
<DATELINE>FORESTVILLE, Md. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A 14-year veteran of the Prince George's
County police force was shot and killed, apparently by a fellow
officer, while executing a search warrant in a drug-related
investigation, Chief Michael J. Flaherty said today.
   Cpl. Mark Kevin Murphy, 35, died at Prince George's Hospital
Center in Cheverly about six hours after Wednesday night's raid of
an apartment complex in nearby Riverdale.
   ``It appears at this time that Corporal Murphy was accidentally
shot by a fellow officer,'' a tearful Flaherty told a news
conference. ``There was one wound, and it appears to be to the rear
of the head.''
   At least two officers were immediately behind Murphy, Flaherty
said.
   One weapon was recovered from the apartment, but it was not
fired during the raid, the chief said.
   Murphy, a member of the Emergency Services Team, was crouched,
attempting to place a hydraulic ram against the apartment door,
when the door suddenly opened, Flaherty said.
   At that point, officers said, they heard what sounded like a
gunshot, Flaherty said. Four shots were fired during the raid, he
added.
   Five men were arrested on drug charges. One suspect was taken to
Prince George's Hospital Center, where he was listed in stable
condition with head injuries.
</TEXT>
