<HEAD>Fire Engulfs North Side Apartment Building</HEAD>
<DATELINE>CHICAGO (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Fire swept through an apartment building early
today, killing three people and injuring nine, authorities said.
   The blaze on the city's North Side burned nearly two hours
before it was brought under control shortly after 1 a.m., said Bill
Crowley, a Fire Department spokesman.
   About 125 firefighters helped rescue residents of the
three-story brick building, and as many as 100 people may have been
left homeless, Crowley said.
   Firefighters encountered a language barrier when they arrived
because most of the building's residents were Korean and spoke
little English, the spokesman said.
   Killed were three residents, ages 85, 60 and 35, officials said.
   Crowley said the blaze apparently started on a rear porch.
