<HEAD>US Concerned About Attacks on Kurdish Rebels</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The United States is concerned about reports
that Iraq may have used chemical weapons in a campaign to suppress
Kurdish rebel groups, the State Department said Thursday.
   ``If the reports are accurate, this is a grave violation of
international human rights standards,'' said spokeswoman Phyllis
Oakley, noting that use of chemical weapons was condemned in a U.N.
