<HEAD>Dukakis Camp Warns Supporters Against Canvassing PAC</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BOSTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The presidential campaign of Michael Dukakis has
cautioned supporters against donating money to Citizens for
Dukakis, an Illinois-based political action committee which has
been conducting a telephone fund-raising effort.
   Daniel Small, general counsel for Dukakis' finance operation,
said the organization is not authorized by the Dukakis campaign or
the Democratic National Committee.
   Small said the campaign has receieved numerous complaints from
people who were solicited by callers for Citizens for Dukakis and
thought they were donating money to the Dukakis campaign.
   ``We have no idea how they spend their money, and we would urge
anyone who wishes to help Mike Dukakis or any Democratic candidate
to contribute their money to the DNC,'' Small said.
   Janet Kelsey, executive director of Citizens for Dukakis,
acknowledged that her organization, which she described as an
independant political action committee, has no connection with the
Dukakis campaign.
   ``We have reviewed this with our telemarketers, and we've put in
some new language'' that makes it clear Citizens for Dukakis is not
connected with the campaign or the DNC, Kelsey said. ``We never
intended to imply a connection.''
