<2ND_LINE>PM-Clothing Workers,0331</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Settlement Between Men's Clothing Manufacturers and Workers</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By MARJORIE ANDERS</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Bargainers for 15,000 garment workers and
several men's clothing manufacturers reached a tentative agreement
this morning on a contract that includes improved wages and health
benefits, a union spokeswoman said.
   The 18-month contract covers members of the Amalgamated Clothing
and Textile Workers Union in a dozen companies across the country,
said the spokeswoman, Jo-Ann Mort.
   The pact is expected to set a pattern for contracts for ACTWU's
other 27,000 members nationwide, she said.
   Jack Sheinkman, president of the union, said wages and health
benefits improved under the new deal, but terms were not disclosed
pending a ratification vote in the next few days.
   The agreement was reached shortly after midnight Wednesday
following a marathon bargaining session, Ms. Mort said.
   Cutters and sewers of men's and boys shirts and men's night wear
currently earn an average of $5.54 an hour, according to the Bureau
of Labor Statistics. The BLS has no wage figures for pants makers.
   The manufacturers, members of the Cotton Garment Allied
Industries Fund, include several big-name makers of men's shirts
and pants including Arrow, Gant and Hathaway.
   The major companies involved in the talks and the locations of
their factories are as follows:
   Jaymar-Ruby of Michigan City, Ind., Elizabethtown, Ky., Rector,
Ark., and Anniston, Ala.
   Hathaway of Waterville, Me.
   Arrow, a subsidiary of Westpoint-Pepperell, of Andalusia,
Jasper, Enterprise and Montgomery in Alabama and Rome and Cedartown
in Georgia.
   Manhattan Industries of Americus, Ga., and Winsboro, S.C.
   Reltok Manufacturing Inc., of Win, Ark., Forrest City, Ark.,
Florence, Ala., Winfield, Tenn., and Beavertorn, Tenn.
   Publix Shirt of Huntington and Columbia in Tennessee and
Meridian, Miss.
   Fishman and Tobin of Orangeburg, S.C.
   Eagle@Gant Shirts of Allentown, Pa.
   Flushing Shirt of Pittsburgh
   B. Lippman Inc., of Frostberg, Md., Grantsville, Md. and
Pittsburgh.
