   The stock market lapsed into a broad decline
today amid renewed worries over the interest-rate outlook.
   The Dow Jones average of 30 industrials fell 10.49 to 2,021.16
in the first half hour of trading.
   Losers outnumbered gainers by nearly 3 to 1 in nationwide
trading of New York Stock Exchange-listed issues, with 230 up, 639
down and 504 unchanged.
   Volume on the Big Board came to 18.45 million shares as of 10
a.m. on Wall Street.
