Friday's report from the government on the employment situation for
August.
   There has been some hope lately that the figures would show a
moderation of job growth, thus relieving some pressure for
credit-tightening by the Federal Reserve.
   But some analysts noted fears that any surprises when the report
is finally issued could upset the markets.
   Losers among the blue chips included International Business
Machines, down } at 110}; Exxon, down \ at 46\, and Philip Morris,
down ] at 91{.
   The NYSE's composite index of all its listed common stocks
dropped .60 to 147.69. At the American Stock Exchange, the market
value index was down .61 at 294.19.
   On Wednesday the Dow Jones industrial average posted a 6.58 loss
to 2,031.65.
   Declining issues slightly outnumbered advances on the New York
Stock Exchange, with 679 up, 706 down and 537 unchanged.
   Big Board volume totaled 130.48 million shares, against 108.72
million in the previous session.
