<1ST_LINE>s f BC-JetLeasing-Firms Adv04   09-01 0342</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>BC-Jet Leasing-Firms, Adv 04,0348</2ND_LINE>
<NOTE>$adv 04</NOTE>
<NOTE>For Release Sunday Sept. 4 and Thereafter</NOTE>
<HEAD>With BC-Jet Leasing Boom</HEAD>
<HEAD>Handful of Companies Dominate Jet Leasing Business</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Although many companies and banks lease planes
to airlines, a handful of specialized firms dominate the business
worldwide. The leading players are:
   _INTERNATIONAL LEASE FINANCE CORP. Based in Beverly Hills,
Calif., the company specializes in short-term operating leases for
aircraft. It has a ``jet portfolio'' of about 60 aircraft worth $2
billion, with another 197 on order. The company has 70 airline
customers, including major U.S. and foreign carriers.
   _GATX AIR. Based in San Francisco, the company is a subsidiary
of financial services company GATX Corp. It has fleet of 52
aircraft, plus 20 advanced Airbus A320s on order. The company has
about 20 airline customers, including nine outside the United
States.
   _GE CAPITAL. Based in Stamford, Conn., the subsidiary of General
Electric Co. deals in leases of every kind, mainly on a long-term
basis similar to an installment plan. It has a subsidiary, Polaris,
which deals in short-term operating leases for used aircraft.
Customer information was not disclosed.
   _GPA GROUP LTD. Based in Shannon, Ireland, this privately held
firm, one of the largest companies in Ireland, specializes in
leasing and other financial services for the aviation industry.
Principle shareholders include Aer Lingus of Ireland, Air Canada,
Long-Term Credit Bank of Japan, Mitsubishi Trust & Banking Corp.
and Prudential Insurance Co. of America. The company has a
portfolio of 117 aircraft worth $2.4 billion, leased to 42 airlines
in 25 countries. Another 252 planes are on order.
   _ANSETT WORLDWIDE AVIATION SERVICES. Based in Sydney, Australia,
the company is a subsidiary of Ansett Transport Industries Ltd., an
Australian conglomerate owned 50-50 by media tycoon Rupert Murdoch
and transportation company TNT Ltd. Ansett Transport owns eight
different airlines. Ansett Worldwide Aviation has about 40 planes
in its fleet and 67 on order. It has around 12 airline customers in
the United States, Brazil, Britain, France, Spain and other
countries.
</TEXT>
<NOTE>End Adv Sunday Sept. 4</NOTE>
