<HEAD>Pernod Ricard SA Buys 2.8 Percent Stake in Irish Distillers</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Pernod Ricard SA, a French drinks company, said
Thursday it has bought a 2.8 percent stake in Irish Distillers
Group PLC, the target of a hostile bid by British drinks company
Grand Metropolitan PLC.
   Pernod Ricard said last week it was holding talks with Irish
Distillers and that it already had bought a near 1 percent stake in
the Irish whiskey producer, fueling speculation it was considering
a friendly counter-bid.
   Grand Metropolitan has said it will not raise its 253
million-Irish-pound offer, equivalent to $359 million, unless a
third party enters the bidding.
   Under a timetable set by the Britain's Panel on Takeovers and
Mergers, Pernod Ricard has until Monday to decide whether to launch
a rival bid for Irish Distillers.
   Pernod said it purchased 1.14 million Irish Distillers shares on
Wednesday at about $5.90 each.
   Irish Distillers said it would welcome a Pernod Ricard bid.
