<HEAD>Auto Production Goes Up This WeekoProdn     09-01</HEAD>
<DATELINE>DETROIT (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Domestic automakers were scheduled to produce
210,484 cars and light trucks this week, up from last week's
200,801, Ward's Automotive Reports said Thursday.
   This week's production is higher than the same week a year ago,
in which 203,041 cars and light trucks were produced, the trade
journal said.
   U.S. automakers were scheduled to make 134,337 cars this week,
compared with 125,606 a week ago and 125,852 in the same week in
1987.
