<1ST_LINE>r f BC-Earns-CadburySchweppes     09-01 0167</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>BC-Earns-Cadbury Schweppes,0174</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Cadbury Schweppes Reports Higher Pretax Profits</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Cadbury Schweppes PLC, a British soft drinks and
confectionery group, on Thursday said its pretax profits jumped 28
percent to 81.7 million pounds, or about $137 million, in the first
half of the year.
   In the year-ago period, the company reported pretax profits of
63.6 million pounds, or $107 million.
   Profits after taxes and minority interests but before
extraordinary items rose 37 percent in the first six months to 53.5
million pound, from 38.8 million pounds.
   Revenue during the period rose 14 percent to 1.06 billion pounds
from 932.9 million pounds in the year-ago period.
   Cadbury, maker of Peter Paul candy bars, recently announced the
sale of its U.S. confectionery operations to Hershey Foods Corp. in
a $300 million deal.
   General Cinema Corp., a Chestnut Hill, Mass.-based concern with
interests in movie theaters and soft drink bottling, has built up a
18.4 percent stake in Cadbury and may be interested in its drinks
business.
</TEXT>
